cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.RO, cs.NE 

The paper presents a modular neural framework for computer vision, specifically for object tracking tasks. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also mentions the use of soft attention mechanisms and gradient descent, which are common techniques in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The framework also involves a recurrent attention module, which is a common technique in robotics (cs.RO). Finally, the paper mentions the use of neural networks, which is a common technique in neural engineering (cs.NE).
